revision.text: ==English== {{wikipedia}} ===Etymology=== From {{bor|en|es|Ybarra}}, variant of the {{der|en|eu|-}} surname {{m|eu|Ibarra}}. ===Proper noun=== {{en-proper noun|Ybarras}} # {{surname|en}}. ====Statistics==== * According to the 2010 United States Census, ''Ybarra'' is the 1619<sup>th</sup> most common surname in the United States, belonging to 22211 individuals. ''Ybarra'' is most common among Hispanic/Latino (88.06%) and White (10.33%) individuals. ===Further reading=== * {{R:en:DAFN}} [[Category:English surnames from Basque]] [[Category:English surnames from Spanish]] ---- ==Spanish== ===Etymology=== Originally an alternative spelling of {{m|es|Ibarra}}, from {{der|es|eu|ibar||hill}}. ===Pronunciation=== {{es-IPA}} ===Proper noun=== {{es-proper noun|f|g2=m}} # {{surname|es}}
